question:
The number of real solutions of the equation $$\eqalign{
  &amp; {\sin ^{ - 1}}\left( {\sum\limits_{i = 1}^\infty  {} {x^{i + 1}} - x\sum\limits_{i = 1}^\infty  {} {{\left( {{x \over 2}} \right)}^i}} \right)  \cr 
  &amp;  = {\pi  \over 2} - {\cos ^1}\left( {\sum\limits_{i = 1}^\infty  {} {{\left( {{{ - x} \over 2}} \right)}^i} - \sum\limits_{i = 1}^\infty  {} {{\left( { - x} \right)}^i}} \right) \cr} $$ lying in the interval $$\left( { - {1 \over 2},{1 \over 2}} \right)$$ is ........... .<br><br>(Here, the inverse trigonometric functions sin<sup>$$-$$1</sup> x and cos<sup>$$-$$1</sup> x assume values in $${\left[ { - {\pi  \over 2},{\pi  \over 2}} \right]}$$ and $${\left[ {0,\pi } \right]}$$, respectively.)

